{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/hello-world/","webpackCompilationHash":"2dbdb8bfbf70e544cb14","result":{"data":{"post":{"id":"efc5b6db-00ab-5773-9661-82d6a76987cb","html":"<p>I’m starting a blog/portfolio of my toy projects, and you’re in its first post! The cute little doggie in the photo is Viola, my friend who lives with me. The picture in the front page is a simulation of surnames dying out in a fixed population through a certain number of epochs.</p>\n<p>The simulation works by creating a population with each entity having a unique id, then for a certain number of iterations, we permute these values and take the first half as those who keep their surnames and the other half as those who adopt the other half’s surname. With this setup the number of surnames rapidly decrease. The surnames were then taken and normalised, being used as a heatmap, which produces the following image:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/13e9bc0b122a951f6ccdade2b1bcdd8a/6da3e/heatrand720.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 55.833333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"heatrand720\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/13e9bc0b122a951f6ccdade2b1bcdd8a/6da3e/heatrand720.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/13e9bc0b122a951f6ccdade2b1bcdd8a/9ec3c/heatrand720.png 200w,\n/static/13e9bc0b122a951f6ccdade2b1bcdd8a/c7805/heatrand720.png 400w,\n/static/13e9bc0b122a951f6ccdade2b1bcdd8a/6da3e/heatrand720.png 720w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Then to achieve the visual effect of a gradient I sort the surnames at each generation, which gives the banner image:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/34064115f4b1895caa2a4e5ba7de36a0/6da3e/heatsort720.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 55.833333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"heatsort720\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/34064115f4b1895caa2a4e5ba7de36a0/6da3e/heatsort720.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/34064115f4b1895caa2a4e5ba7de36a0/9ec3c/heatsort720.png 200w,\n/static/34064115f4b1895caa2a4e5ba7de36a0/c7805/heatsort720.png 400w,\n/static/34064115f4b1895caa2a4e5ba7de36a0/6da3e/heatsort720.png 720w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>It also helps to sort these values when visualising how the population dies out, by assigning each id with a random color instead of a gradient:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a1bd8da870340f4077232fce3b116387/6da3e/plotsort720.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 55.833333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"plotsort720\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/a1bd8da870340f4077232fce3b116387/6da3e/plotsort720.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a1bd8da870340f4077232fce3b116387/9ec3c/plotsort720.png 200w,\n/static/a1bd8da870340f4077232fce3b116387/c7805/plotsort720.png 400w,\n/static/a1bd8da870340f4077232fce3b116387/6da3e/plotsort720.png 720w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>This blog is made using <a href=\"gatsbyjs.org\">Gatsby</a> with the <a href=\"github.com/greglobinski/gatsby-starter-hero-blog\">HeroBlog</a> starter by <a href=\"github.com/greglobinski\">Greg Lobinsky</a>. If you’re seeing this, Greg, thank you for the starter!</p>","fields":{"slug":"/hello-world/","prefix":"2019-06-14"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Hello World","author":"Pedro HC Avelar","category":"etc","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/1827a96cf40bbf251b4c6a17859a6f4c/c83a6/viols.jpg"}}}}},"authornote":{"id":"a8fd85a3-d2b3-53af-9552-8d987b901a21","html":"<p><strong>Pedro HC Avelar</strong> Computer Science PhD Candidate @ UFRGS</p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"facebook":{"appId":""}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/hello-world/","prev":{"id":"c598878a-08a2-5bee-b810-5415775485ad","fields":{"slug":"/draft-post/","prefix":"","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"This is a draft post","category":"sayings"}},"next":{"id":"abe9d629-1fc5-5c8b-afa2-54ed6803860a","fields":{"slug":"/Neural-Style-Transfer-1/","prefix":"2019-06-15","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Neural Style Transfer, Part 1","category":"Deep Learning"}},"source":"posts"}}}